==English==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ə/}}

===Etymology 1===
Old English [[-ere]], from Germanic.

====Suffix====
'''-er''' ''(productive)''

#Forming nouns from nouns and adjectives with the sense of ‘person or thing connected or involved with, belonging to, having’
#:''New Yorker'', ''astrologer'', ''cricketer'', ''six-footer'', ''three-wheeler''
#Forming nouns from verbs with the sense of ‘person or thing which does’
#:''reader'', ''cooker'', ''computer'', ''runner-up'', ''do-gooder''

=====Usage notes=====
#The suffix may be used to form an agent noun of any verb.  In compound or phrasal verbs, the suffix usually follows the verb component (as in '''passerby''' and '''runner-up''') but is sometimes added at the end, irrespective of the position of the verb component ('''do-gooder''') or is added to both components for humorous effect ('''washer-upper''').

